# i18n & Festival content

## i18n

- Catalog: `src/i18n/en.ts` (source of truth for keys), `src/i18n/vi.ts` must mirror all keys
- UI strings: `data-i18n` attributes or `t('key')` — never hardcode user-facing text
- Locale refresh: `registerLocaleRefresh()` re-applies strings on EN/VN toggle

## Festival article

- **Canonical in-app:** `src/content/festival/en.md` and `vi.md`
- Rendered via `festivalContent.ts` with stable section IDs (`FESTIVAL_SECTION_IDS`)
- `FestivalScreen` preserves scroll anchor on locale change
- Repo essay `le-hoi-ooc-om-boc.md` is bilingual combined — keep synced with in-app files

## Cultural notes

- Oóc Om Bóc / Oc Om Bok — Khmer festival in Mekong Delta
- Game is educational, not an official event site
- Some mechanics are simplified vs real festival
